Definition.WordDefinition: sec adj : (of champagne) moderately dry [syn: {unsweet}] n 1: 1/60 of a minute; the basic unit of time adopted under the Systeme International d'Unites [syn: {second}, {s}] 2: ratio of the hypotenuse to the adjacent side of a right-angled triangle [syn: {secant}] 3: an independent federal agency that oversees the exchange of securities to protect investors [syn: {Securities and Exchange Commission}]
